South Africa’s Trade Minister Says Rand Volatility a ‘Problem’

-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 
2011-10-14T12:51:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/south-africa-s-trade-minister-says-rand-volatility-a-problem-.html
South African Trade and Industry
Minister  Rob Davies  said while the rand has depreciated, it is
still a “problem” because it has become more volatile.  The government is looking at concerns raised by
manufacturers about high port costs and power prices, Davies
told reporters today in  Cape Town .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mike Cohen in Cape Town at 
